(Make your DVD drive Region-Free!)<br />
<br />
Making your DVD drive region-free is a fairly simple and straightforward procedure.<br />
<img src=http://www.dvdhelp.us/graphics/screenshots/dvdidle_rf.gif><br />
<br />
First, make sure that you have selected the correct DVD Drive. You can click the &quot;Region Info&quot; button for further information about your drive's current Region Info.<br />
<br />
Second, make sure that you check all of the boxes as shown above in order to get the maximum benefit from this software.<br />
<br />
<img src=http://www.dvdhelp.us/graphics/screenshots/dvdidle_rf2.gif><br />
<br />
In order to get the maximum benefit from DVD Region-Free, I recommend that you do not stray from the settings above unless you are fairly experienced, and fully understand what they represent.<br />
<br />
If you experience trouble with the &quot;Region-Free for RCE DVDs&quot; setting, you may manually set this to your region.<br />
<br />
DVD Region-Free allows you to manually add your DVD player, if it is not listed by default. Normally, you will not have to edit this section at all.<br />
<br />
<img src=http://www.dvdhelp.us/graphics/screenshots/dvdidle_rf3.gif><br />
<br />
Assuming your DVD Player is listed (or manually added, if necessary) simply click &quot;OK&quot; and you'll be on your way to a whole new world of Region-Free DVD enjoyment.<br />
